30/01/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Opposition lawmakers decided Friday (28 January) to launch a joint initiative for a no-confidence motion against Parliamentary Speaker Ognyan Gerdzhikov and the government of Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg.
The move follows a failed parliamentary hearing on tobacco privatisation.
In other news, the Bulgarian Army has signed a contract to purchase 18 transport helicopters from Eurocopter, a European consortium.
The order includes six Panther AS323s for the Navy and 12 Cougar AS352s for the ground forces.
(Sega - 29/01/05;
AFP, Mediapool, bTV - 28/01/05)
